Argentina has defaulted for the second time in 12 years after last-ditch talks with what it called 'vulture' creditors failed.

The failure follows accusations that president Cristina Fernandez de Kirchner spent close to £20,000 a 
day having the presidential plane bring her the daily newspapers while she was on holiday.

