Argentina failed to strike a deal in time to meet a midnight payment deadline after a long legal battle with hedge funds that rejected its debt restructuring following a 2002 default.

Argentina fought to suspend a U.S ruling requiring it to pay holdouts of $1.33 billion plus 
interest and preventing it from servicing its exchange debt without paying the holdouts at the same time.

